   <concept id="FAR_9_406_4"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">9.406-4</ph> Period of debarment.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d589e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d616e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d589e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e15" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Debarment shall
be for a period commensurate with the seriousness of the cause(s).
Generally, debarment should not exceed 3 years, except that-</p>
                     <ol id="d589e33" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d616e21" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Debarment
for violation of the provisions of <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?path=/prelim@title41/subtitle4/chapter81&amp;edition=prelim"
                                    format="html"
                                    scope="external"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 81</xref>,
Drug-Free Workplace (see <xref href="23.506.dita#FAR_23_506"
                                    base="i1094606"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">23.506</xref>)
may be for a period not to exceed 5 years;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d616e32" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Debarments
under <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                                    base="i1115334"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">9.406-2</xref>(b)(2) shall be
for 1 year unless extended pursuant to paragraph (b) of this section;
and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d616e40" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2021-03 February 16, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">Debarments <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2017-018?>under <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                                       base="i1115334"
                                       outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">9.406-2</xref>(b)(1)(vii) shall
be for a period of not less than 2 years, inclusive of any suspension period,
if suspension precedes a debarment (see paragraph (a)(2) of this
section).<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 9.406-4 by revising paragraph (a)(1)(iii).?></ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e52" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> If suspension
precedes a debarment, the suspension period shall be considered
in determining the debarment period.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d616e57" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The debarring
official may extend the debarment for an additional period, if that
official determines that an extension is necessary to protect the
Government’s interest. However, a debarment may not be extended
solely on the basis of the facts and circumstances upon which the
initial debarment action was based. Debarments under <xref href="9.406-2.dita#FAR_9_406_2"
                        base="i1115334"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.406-2</xref>(b)(2) may be extended
for additional periods of one year if the Secretary of Homeland
Security or the Attorney General determines that the contractor
continues to be in violation of the employment provisions of the
Immigration and Nationality Act. If debarment for an additional
period is determined to be necessary, the procedures of <xref href="9.406-3.dita#FAR_9_406_3"
                        base="i1115383"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.406-3</xref> shall be followed
to extend the debarment.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d616e68" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> The debarring
official may reduce the period or extent of debarment, upon the
contractor’s request, supported by documentation, for reasons such
as-</p>
               <ol id="d589e95" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e74" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Newly
discovered material evidence;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e79" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Reversal
of the conviction or civil judgment upon which the debarment was
based;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Bona fide
change in ownership or management;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e89" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Elimination
of other causes for which the debarment was imposed; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d616e94" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph> Other reasons
the debarring official deems appropriate.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
